    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomatoes </strong>into wedges</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms</strong> to the dish with your<strong> dried oregano</strong>,<strong> bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>baharat</strong> and cook for 1-2 min until very lightly browned all over</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into rings</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper rings</strong> and<strong> tomato wedges</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good stir</p><p>Put the dish in the oven, uncovered, for an initial 15 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and set aside for later \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 15 min, remove the dish from the oven and stir through your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> and <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and return the dish to the oven for 15 min further \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot</strong> <strong>Turkish-style Fable mushroom bulgur pilaf</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>mint leaves </strong>finely, discard the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After a further 15 min, remove the dish from the oven and leave to stand (keep the lid on!) for another 10 min</p><p>Tip: This will help to make the bulgur fluffy!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-turkish-style-fable-mushroom-bulgur-pilaf/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, fluff the <strong>one pot Turkish-style Fable mushroom bulgur pilaf </strong>with a fork</p><p>Dollop your<strong> natural yoghurt </strong>over the top and scatter the<strong> chopped mint </strong>all over</p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>sumac</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
